    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the depth and complexity can change, but it's not always a massive shift. In the VP-attachment reading, the structure tends to be deeper because the PP is incorporated as an adjunct *within* the larger VP framework. The NP attachment keeps the PP closer to the noun it modifies, potentially keeping that specific subtree shallower. Think of it this way: attaching to the VP adds a layer of modification *to the action*, whereas attaching to the NP adds a layer of description *to the noun*.",
      "source": "target",
